{"mode":"repetition","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Test your knowledge on Measurement<\/strong><\/p>\n","dialogs":[{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is m<\/strong><strong>easurement?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Measurement is known as measuring the size or the amount of something.<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60d8664306d09.gif","mime":"image\/gif","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":400,"height":300},"audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e2e82d7f425.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}]},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What are the types of measurement?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1) Standard measurement<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>2) Non-standard measurement<\/strong><\/p>\n","audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e2f7b981333.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}],"image":{"path":"images\/image-60f3ae4835f20.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":512,"height":512}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is Non-standard measurement?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Anything that you can find that helps you measure objects. These don't have numbers on them.<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60e2ebadee1ef.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":891,"height":408,"originalImage":{"path":"images\/image-60d8675320b4b.png","mime":"image\/png","height":569,"width":1108}},"audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e2f8ad49df2.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}]},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What are some examples of non-standard measurement?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Armspan, Handspan, Cubit, Pace, Footspan, etc.<\/strong><\/p>\n","audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e2e9279f00f.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}],"image":{"path":"images\/image-659ee26422d9b.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":512,"height":512}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is handspan?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The distance between the thumb and the little finger when it is stretched is known as handspan.<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60e2e3bdc7362.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":289,"height":460,"originalImage":{"path":"images\/image-60e2e3aecf808.png#tmp","mime":"image\/png","height":839,"width":1429}},"audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e2e97ae5b51.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}]},{"tips":{},"image":{"path":"images\/image-60e2e42578ed9.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":474,"height":395,"originalImage":{"path":"images\/image-60e2e41752beb.png#tmp","mime":"image\/png","height":839,"width":1429}},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is cubit?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The length of a forearm, that is,&nbsp;the length from the elbow to the fingertip is known as cubit.<\/strong><\/p>\n","audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e2e9bfb3101.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}]},{"tips":{},"image":{"path":"images\/image-60e2e476099bd.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":608,"height":444,"originalImage":{"path":"images\/image-60e2e467b6969.png#tmp","mime":"image\/png","height":839,"width":1429}},"answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The length of a person's outstretched arms, measured from the fingertips is called armspan.<\/strong><\/p>\n","text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is armspan?<\/strong><\/p>\n","audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e2ea0269a94.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{